521
00:55:16,827 --> 00:55:17,867
You smell bad.

522
00:55:18,914 --> 00:55:20,454
I've never bathed much.

523
00:55:22,948 --> 00:55:27,868
Those weird hairs that grew out
of your back, I took them to a lab.

524
00:55:28,071 --> 00:55:29,951
I had them analyzed.

525
00:55:33,234 --> 00:55:34,944
The hairs?

526
00:55:36,190 --> 00:55:38,070
The hairs?

527
00:55:38,487 --> 00:55:41,617
Oh, yeah.
That's a strange thing to do.

528
00:55:41,812 --> 00:55:44,112
Not as strange as the results.

529
00:55:44,568 --> 00:55:47,238
The guy had trouble identifying them.

530
00:55:47,894 --> 00:55:51,694
He finally concluded that they
were definitely not human.

531
00:55:54,185 --> 00:55:56,815
-Very good.
-Not human, Seth.

532
00:55:57,101 --> 00:56:01,151
In fact, very likely insect hairs.

533
00:56:01,805 --> 00:56:03,315
That's ridiculous.

534
00:56:03,562 --> 00:56:04,772
Look.

535
00:56:05,390 --> 00:56:07,560
There's more. Look at your face.

536
00:56:08,645 --> 00:56:10,395
Something happened.

537
00:56:10,642 --> 00:56:13,262
You need help. You must be sick.

538
00:56:13,468 --> 00:56:15,138
You're jealous!

539
00:56:18,092 --> 00:56:20,852
I've become free
and you can't stand it.

540
00:56:21,098 --> 00:56:23,258
You'll do anything to bring me down.

541
00:56:25,132 --> 00:56:27,802
Does this look like a sick man to you?

542
00:56:29,886 --> 00:56:31,386
No, stop it!

543
00:56:31,633 --> 00:56:33,253
Can a sick man do that?

544
00:56:34,090 --> 00:56:36,800
The deal is off.
I don't need you anymore.

545
00:56:38,424 --> 00:56:40,504
Seth, please, wait. Seth!

546
00:56:40,750 --> 00:56:41,880
Don't come back.

547
00:56:43,047 --> 00:56:44,707
Oh, God....

548
00:58:57,660 --> 00:58:59,030
Oh, no.

549
00:59:00,986 --> 00:59:03,406
What's happening to me? Am I dying?

550
00:59:05,779 --> 00:59:07,989
Is this how it starts? Am I dying?

551
00:59:11,531 --> 00:59:13,191
Brundle, Seth.

552
00:59:14,397 --> 00:59:16,107
Give me a disc.

553
00:59:17,023 --> 00:59:19,653
I need the first
teleportation: S. Brundle.

554
00:59:55,680 --> 00:59:57,100
Run sequence.

555
01:01:50,341 --> 01:01:51,591
Hello.

556
01:01:55,254 --> 01:01:56,594
Seth.

557
01:01:58,919 --> 01:02:02,839
Seth, I've been trying to reach you.
Where are you?

558
01:02:03,043 --> 01:02:04,963
I've been afraid to see you.

559
01:02:05,210 --> 01:02:09,800
Now I'm afraid not to.

560
01:02:10,003 --> 01:02:11,423
Are you at home?

561
01:02:11,581 --> 01:02:13,671
You don't know how right you were.

562
01:02:13,878 --> 01:02:15,538
I've gotten...

563
01:02:15,995 --> 01:02:18,585
...much, much worse.

564
01:02:18,831 --> 01:02:21,161
Please come see me.

565
01:02:21,418 --> 01:02:23,248
Please come now.

566
01:02:47,901 --> 01:02:49,321
Seth?

567
01:02:49,948 --> 01:02:50,988
I'm here.

568
01:02:51,236 --> 01:02:52,406
Stop!

569
01:02:59,145 --> 01:03:00,985
You were right.

570
01:03:01,192 --> 01:03:03,272
I'm diseased...

571
01:03:04,148 --> 01:03:06,568
...and it might be contagious somehow.

572
01:03:07,983 --> 01:03:10,143
I wouldn't want to infect you.

573
01:03:12,437 --> 01:03:14,687
And it's been accelerating.

574
01:03:15,263 --> 01:03:18,893
It's unrelenting.
Every day there are changes.

575
01:03:19,057 --> 01:03:22,597
Every time I look in the mirror,
I'm someone different, repulsive.

576
01:03:22,842 --> 01:03:23,802
What happened?

577
01:03:24,051 --> 01:03:28,021
I know an old lady who swallowed a fly
Perhaps she'll de

578
01:03:28,844 --> 01:03:31,554
Seth, please.

579
01:03:32,639 --> 01:03:36,809
I was not pure. The teleporter
insists on purity. I was not pure.

580
01:03:38,720 --> 01:03:40,470
I don't know what you mean.

581
01:03:43,294 --> 01:03:45,134
A fly...

582
01:03:45,671 --> 01:03:50,761
...got into the transmitter pod with
me that first time when I was alone.

583
01:03:54,339 --> 01:03:56,959
The computer got confused.

584
01:03:57,165 --> 01:04:00,465
There weren't supposed
to be two genetic patterns.

585
01:04:00,620 --> 01:04:04,090
And it decided to splice us together.

586
01:04:04,744 --> 01:04:06,584
It mated us, me and the fly.

587
01:04:06,791 --> 01:04:08,871
We hadn't been properly introduced.

588
01:04:12,783 --> 01:04:16,753
My teleporter turned
into a gene splicer.

589
01:04:17,536 --> 01:04:20,916
A very good one.
I'm not Seth Brundle anymore.

590
01:04:22,370 --> 01:04:25,660
I'm the offspring
of Brundle and a housefly.

591
01:04:27,532 --> 01:04:30,742
Oh, God. Oh, God, Seth!

592
01:04:30,988 --> 01:04:32,828
You look so pretty.

593
01:04:33,364 --> 01:04:35,114
What will happen?

594
01:04:35,571 --> 01:04:38,861
I think it's showing itself
as a bizarre form of cancer.

595
01:04:39,446 --> 01:04:44,276
General cellular chaos and revolution.
I'm just gonna disintegrate.

596
01:04:44,479 --> 01:04:46,569
In a novel way, no doubt.

597
01:04:47,435 --> 01:04:48,525
Then I'll die.

598
01:04:49,232 --> 01:04:53,022
-And then it will be over.
-No, I don't accept that.

599
01:04:53,267 --> 01:04:56,987
There must be something we can do,
someone to go to, tests to be done.

600
01:04:57,181 --> 01:05:01,771
No! I won't be
just another tumorous bore...

601
01:05:01,975 --> 01:05:06,145
...talking about his hair falling out
and his lost lymph nodes.

602
01:05:07,097 --> 01:05:09,477
What do you want me to do?
Why did you call me?

603
01:05:26,800 --> 01:05:28,130
That's disgusting.

604
01:05:38,424 --> 01:05:39,634
My...

605
01:05:40,421 --> 01:05:42,251
...ear. No!

606
01:05:43,457 --> 01:05:45,297
I'm scared.

607
01:05:48,620 --> 01:05:49,880
Help me.

608
01:05:51,246 --> 01:05:54,456
Please, please, help me.

609
01:06:02,700 --> 01:06:06,250
-Don't go back to him.
-That's it?

610
01:06:06,455 --> 01:06:07,535
That's your advice?

611
01:06:07,743 --> 01:06:10,873
It could be contagious.
It could become an epidemic.

612
01:06:11,079 --> 01:06:12,829
I have to go back to him.

613
01:06:13,366 --> 01:06:16,906
-I don't believe this.
-If you saw him, Stathis....

614
01:06:17,150 --> 01:06:20,700
If you saw how scared and angry
and desperate he is--

615
01:06:20,945 --> 01:06:23,825
I'm sure Typhoid Mary was nice
when you saw her socially.

616
01:06:24,071 --> 01:06:26,151
-I do not want--
-I don't care!

617
01:06:26,357 --> 01:06:28,357
All right, fine, okay.

618
01:06:42,146 --> 01:06:44,606
Do I have permission to claim
your body when this is over?

619
01:06:45,641 --> 01:06:47,481
Oh, God....

620
01:06:50,304 --> 01:06:52,144
Look, how about this?

621
01:06:54,888 --> 01:06:57,938
You say, if only I saw him.

622
01:06:58,433 --> 01:06:59,853
Show me.

623
01:07:00,680 --> 01:07:02,100
Tape him. Show me.

624
01:07:02,887 --> 01:07:04,637
Let me think about it.

625
01:07:06,552 --> 01:07:08,392
I'll come up with something.

626
01:07:35,621 --> 01:07:36,871
Seth?

627
01:07:43,620 --> 01:07:44,620
Seth?

628
01:07:44,868 --> 01:07:46,868
No, no, no. Up here.

629
01:07:50,371 --> 01:07:52,371
I've gotten pretty good at it.

630
01:07:53,077 --> 01:07:55,247
Yeah, it's almost second nature.

631
01:07:56,363 --> 01:07:58,533
I stopped biting my nails.

632
01:08:03,612 --> 01:08:05,702
Look at this. What's this?

633
01:08:06,818 --> 01:08:08,028
I don't know.

634
01:08:11,941 --> 01:08:15,401
I seem to be stricken by a disease
with a purpose, wouldn't you say?

635
01:08:20,070 --> 01:08:23,530
Maybe not such a bad disease
after all.

636
01:08:24,144 --> 01:08:25,234
I can't stay.

637
01:08:25,772 --> 01:08:26,852
No, no, no.

638
01:08:28,608 --> 01:08:30,188
Why not? Why can't you?

639
01:08:30,685 --> 01:08:32,355
I can't take it. It's too much.

640
01:08:32,562 --> 01:08:35,142
Why? The disease
has revealed its purpose.

641
01:08:35,348 --> 01:08:39,768
We don't have to worry about
contagion. I know what it wants.

642
01:08:40,262 --> 01:08:41,602
What does it want?

643
01:08:42,219 --> 01:08:46,229
It wants to turn me
into something else.

644
01:08:46,802 --> 01:08:49,762
Most people would give anything
to be something else.

645
01:08:50,008 --> 01:08:51,428
Turned into what?

646
01:08:51,636 --> 01:08:55,806
What do you think, a fly?
Am I becoming a 185-pound fly?

647
01:08:56,679 --> 01:08:59,259
No, I'm becoming something
that never existed.

648
01:08:59,505 --> 01:09:01,965
I'm becoming "Brundlefly."

649
01:09:03,300 --> 01:09:05,220
That's worth a Nobel Prize.

650
01:09:06,925 --> 01:09:08,255
Here.

651
01:09:08,792 --> 01:09:12,092
I want to give a demonstration...

652
01:09:12,257 --> 01:09:17,387
...that I think you'll want
to record for posterity.

653
01:09:18,089 --> 01:09:20,249
I think you must chronicle...

654
01:09:20,456 --> 01:09:23,506
...the life and times of Brundlefly,
don't you?

655
01:09:24,121 --> 01:09:28,291
At the very least, it should make
a fabulous children's book.

656
01:09:28,874 --> 01:09:29,994
You seem tired.

657
01:09:32,080 --> 01:09:33,210
You got me there?

658
01:09:39,160 --> 01:09:41,160
How does Brundlefly eat?

659
01:09:41,367 --> 01:09:44,327
He found out the hard way
that he eats like a fly eats.

660
01:09:44,532 --> 01:09:46,282
His teeth are now useless.

661
01:09:46,490 --> 01:09:49,950
Although he can chew up
solid food, he can't digest it.

662
01:09:50,194 --> 01:09:53,574
Solid food hurts. So, like a fly...

663
01:09:53,780 --> 01:09:58,280
...Brundlefly breaks down solids
with a corrosive enzyme...

664
01:09:58,523 --> 01:10:00,783
...playfully called "vomit drop. "

665
01:10:00,990 --> 01:10:03,950
He regurgitates on his food.
It liquifies.

666
01:10:04,275 --> 01:10:06,615
And then he sucks back up.

667
01:10:07,271 --> 01:10:09,361
Ready for a demonstration, kids?

668
01:10:10,027 --> 01:10:11,607
Here it goes.

669
01:10:12,943 --> 01:10:15,193
Oh, my God.

670
01:10:16,688 --> 01:10:18,268
My God!

671
01:10:25,765 --> 01:10:27,265
Hey, Ronnie.

672
01:10:30,638 --> 01:10:32,058
Ronnie!

673
01:10:40,595 --> 01:10:42,015
What is it?

674
01:10:48,923 --> 01:10:50,343
I'm pregnant.

675
01:10:51,469 --> 01:10:53,299
Oh, no.

676
01:10:56,423 --> 01:10:57,843
Oh, no.

677
01:11:00,297 --> 01:11:02,627
I'm pregnant with Seth's baby.

678
01:11:11,332 --> 01:11:12,832
What do you want to do?

679
01:11:15,915 --> 01:11:17,205
I don't know.

680
01:11:20,160 --> 01:11:21,830
I just....

681
01:11:21,997 --> 01:11:23,497
I don't know.

682
01:11:51,147 --> 01:11:54,907
-Stathis, I'm scared.
-It's going to be all right, Ronnie.

683
01:11:55,521 --> 01:11:57,191
It's going to be fine.

684
01:11:57,398 --> 01:11:59,568
I don't think I want to lose it.

685
01:11:59,775 --> 01:12:04,115
-Why am I losing it?
-It's better this way. You'll see.

686
01:12:05,147 --> 01:12:07,397
It's the best thing that could happen.

687
01:12:08,143 --> 01:12:12,903
She's expelling it. It's coming out.
I don't think we'll have to go in.

688
01:12:13,096 --> 01:12:16,146
It's gonna be easy.
Don't worry, honey.

689
01:12:16,851 --> 01:12:20,141
No. Please, no.

690
01:12:20,636 --> 01:12:22,396
It'll be over soon. Here we go.

691
01:12:27,057 --> 01:12:29,927
A little suction here.
A little suction.

692
01:12:32,469 --> 01:12:35,009
Hold on a minute.
There's more in there.

693
01:12:35,505 --> 01:12:39,135
-There's more?
-Yeah, I mean a lot more. Okay.

694
01:12:40,009 --> 01:12:42,089
You're gonna have to help us.
Push.

695
01:12:42,336 --> 01:12:44,886
Push it out. Come on, push.

696
01:12:45,132 --> 01:12:48,262
-That's it. Come on, push.
-No, wait.

697
01:12:48,667 --> 01:12:51,377
Give us a push. You can push it out.
Come on.

698
01:12:51,543 --> 01:12:53,793
No, wait, wait. No.

699
01:12:53,999 --> 01:12:55,289
You can do it.

700
01:12:55,747 --> 01:12:57,047
Wait.

701
01:12:58,793 --> 01:13:00,293
No!

702
01:14:11,761 --> 01:14:14,561
I want a disc.
Give me preliminary integration.

703
01:14:14,717 --> 01:14:16,977
I want a disc.
Give me preliminary integration.

704
01:15:01,742 --> 01:15:05,702
You're relics. Yes, you are.
You can't deny it.

705
01:15:05,946 --> 01:15:10,876
Vestigial, archaeological, redundant.

706
01:15:14,035 --> 01:15:16,495
Artifacts of a bygone era.

707
01:15:16,781 --> 01:15:19,201
Of historical interest only.

708
01:15:41,057 --> 01:15:43,357
You've missed some good moments.

709
01:15:44,473 --> 01:15:46,893
Is that why you're here? To catch up?

710
01:15:52,062 --> 01:15:53,352
I wanted....

711
01:15:59,592 --> 01:16:01,762
My teeth have begun to fall out.

712
01:16:03,766 --> 01:16:07,556
The medicine cabinet's now
the Brundle Museum of Natural History.

713
01:16:07,800 --> 01:16:08,930
Want to see it?

714
01:16:09,887 --> 01:16:11,297
No.

715
01:16:13,712 --> 01:16:14,802
Then...

716
01:16:16,758 --> 01:16:18,178
...what do you want?

717
01:16:21,252 --> 01:16:23,962
I came to tell you....

718
01:16:29,460 --> 01:16:31,460
I just....

719
01:16:32,995 --> 01:16:35,965
I wanted to see you...

720
01:16:36,121 --> 01:16:37,711
...before....

721
01:16:46,537 --> 01:16:48,367
You have to leave now...

722
01:16:50,072 --> 01:16:51,742
...and never come back here.

723
01:16:56,533 --> 01:17:00,413
Have you heard of insect politics?

724
01:17:02,484 --> 01:17:03,994
Neither have I.

725
01:17:07,697 --> 01:17:11,657
Insects don't have politics.

726
01:17:13,070 --> 01:17:15,610
They're very brutal.

727
01:17:16,814 --> 01:17:18,564
No compassion.

728
01:17:18,732 --> 01:17:20,822
No compromise.

729
01:17:21,937 --> 01:17:24,357
We can't trust the insect.

730
01:17:27,100 --> 01:17:28,940
I'd like to become...

731
01:17:29,727 --> 01:17:33,107
...the first insect politician.

732
01:17:34,430 --> 01:17:36,270
I'd like to...

733
01:17:38,934 --> 01:17:40,434
...but I'm afraid....

734
01:17:41,680 --> 01:17:44,060
I don't know
what you're trying to say.

735
01:17:45,435 --> 01:17:46,845
I'm saying....

736
01:17:55,051 --> 01:17:57,471
I'm saying I'm an insect...

737
01:17:58,796 --> 01:18:02,556
...who dreamt he was a man
and loved it.

738
01:18:02,801 --> 01:18:04,971
But now the dream is over...

739
01:18:05,377 --> 01:18:07,047
...and the insect is awake.

740
01:18:08,593 --> 01:18:10,173
No, Seth.

741
01:18:11,878 --> 01:18:13,718
I'm saying...

742
01:18:16,372 --> 01:18:18,712
...I'll hurt you if you stay.

743
01:18:58,064 --> 01:19:00,074
Let's go. Let's do it now.

744
01:19:00,231 --> 01:19:03,281
Now? Wait.
Wait a minute. What did he say?

745
01:19:03,896 --> 01:19:06,616
I couldn't tell him.
Let's go, damn it.

746
01:19:06,812 --> 01:19:09,442
No! I think we should
wait a few days.

747
01:19:09,688 --> 01:19:11,278
You're not
in the right state of mind.

748
01:19:11,855 --> 01:19:14,815
I want it out of my body now.
You should have seen him.

749
01:19:15,020 --> 01:19:17,480
There could be anything in here,
in me, in my body.

750
01:19:17,727 --> 01:19:20,777
I don't know if I can
arrange it now, tonight.

751
01:19:20,972 --> 01:19:22,232
Why do we have to--?

752
01:19:22,430 --> 01:19:27,560
I don't want it. Understand?
I don't want it in my body!

753
01:20:01,456 --> 01:20:04,336
Well, okay, what's the story?

754
01:20:07,088 --> 01:20:09,338
She's pregnant
and she wants an abortion.

755
01:20:09,874 --> 01:20:11,294
In the middle of the night?

756
01:20:13,459 --> 01:20:15,749
We have good reason to think that...

757
01:20:15,956 --> 01:20:19,496
...this child will be deformed.

758
01:20:19,910 --> 01:20:22,870
-Yeah, but in the middle of the night?
-Look, Brent.

759
01:20:24,913 --> 01:20:26,033
Please.

760
01:20:28,329 --> 01:20:29,409
Is it your child?

761
01:20:30,406 --> 01:20:31,366
No.

762
01:20:34,740 --> 01:20:39,080
It's the child of a man
who is deformed.

763
01:20:40,781 --> 01:20:42,281
I don't mean to interfere...

764
01:20:42,449 --> 01:20:46,369
...but I detect a certain
uncertainty here.

765
01:20:46,613 --> 01:20:49,483
There are tests we can do
to determine whether--

766
01:20:49,729 --> 01:20:53,909
I don't want tests.
Tests can't guarantee anything.

767
01:20:54,233 --> 01:20:57,443
The baby could start off normal,
then become....

768
01:21:00,524 --> 01:21:02,024
I want an abortion.

769
01:21:04,978 --> 01:21:07,228
I'll do it myself if I have to.

770
01:21:08,313 --> 01:21:12,193
If you'll slip into that,
we'll be on our way in no time.

771
01:21:39,050 --> 01:21:40,090
No.

772
01:21:43,714 --> 01:21:45,714
Wait, Seth, no.

773
01:22:11,286 --> 01:22:13,626
Why did you want to kill Brundle?

774
01:22:14,831 --> 01:22:19,871
The baby might be all that's left
of the real me.

775
01:22:22,660 --> 01:22:24,070
Please don't kill me.

776
01:22:25,736 --> 01:22:29,036
I can't have it. I'm afraid.

777
01:22:29,321 --> 01:22:33,031
Please, have the baby.

778
01:22:33,774 --> 01:22:34,824
I can't.

779
01:22:35,362 --> 01:22:37,192
I can't.

780
01:22:39,107 --> 01:22:40,697
Too bad.

781
01:22:45,568 --> 01:22:47,148
Too bad.

782
01:25:08,719 --> 01:25:10,219
Jesus!

783
01:26:18,942 --> 01:26:22,322
No, don't. Don't, please.

